{
  "name": "Acorn Plans — Inbox → Automated Drawing",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Automated AI Draft — n8n feeds the sketch, container draws\n\n**Flow:** poll the Plans inbox → pull the N-number → take the first image attachment → download it → SSH-upload it to the server `/tmp` → `docker cp` into the **plangenration** container → `docker exec … src/process_plan.py \"<N>\" --image /tmp/<file>` → mark the email read on success.\n\nThe container processes projects at status **Scheduled** for every client while `PLAN_REQUIRE_WATES_CLIENT=false`, then draws floors and uploads the VSDX to SharePoint. AlphaTracker file upload and the Plans Drawn status update are currently disabled. It never reads the mailbox; n8n supplies the image.\n\n### Credentials\n- Outlook: **Plans-Acornhealthandsafety**\n- SSH: **Acorn n8n Server SSH**\n\n### ⚠️ Verify in the UI (SSH file node schema varies by version)\nOn **Upload sketch (SSH)**: Resource = File, Operation = Upload, Input Binary Field = `data`, Target Directory = `/tmp`. The SSH user must be able to write `/tmp` (n8nuser cannot write /opt/acorn — that is why we use /tmp).\n\n### Mark-read rule\nThe container prints ONE JSON line. stdout matching `\"ok\": true` or `\"skipped\": true` → mark read; anything else → leave unread to retry next poll.",
        "height": 440,
        "width": 480
      },
      "id": "note_overview",
      "name": "README",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-560, 0]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "rule": {
          "interval": [
            {
              "field": "minutes",
              "minutesInterval": 15
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "schedule_trigger",
      "name": "Every 15 min",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.scheduleTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1.2,
      "position": [-160, 340]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "getAll",
        "limit": 1,
        "filters": {
          "readStatus": "unread",
          "hasAttachments": true
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.microsoftOutlook",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [60, 340],
      "id": "get_messages",
      "name": "Get unread Plans emails",
      "credentials": {
        "microsoftOutlookOAuth2Api": {
          "id": "FNq1tabrcjylXbSd",
          "name": "Plans-Acornhealthandsafety"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Pull the N-number from each plan email; drop emails without one.\nconst out = [];\nconst items = $input.all();\nfor (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {\n  const j = items[i].json;\n  const text = `${j.subject || ''} ${j.bodyPreview || ''}`;\n  const m = text.match(/N-\\d{4,10}/i);\n  if (!m) continue;\n  out.push({\n    json: { projectNumber: m[0].toUpperCase(), messageId: j.id, subject: j.subject || '' },\n    pairedItem: { item: i },\n  });\n}\nreturn out;"
      },
      "id": "extract_n_number",
      "name": "Extract N-number",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [280, 340]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "messageAttachment",
        "operation": "getAll",
        "messageId": {
          "__rl": true,
          "value": "={{ $json.messageId }}",
          "mode": "id"
        },
        "returnAll": true,
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.microsoftOutlook",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [500, 340],
      "id": "get_attachments",
      "name": "Get attachments",
      "credentials": {
        "microsoftOutlookOAuth2Api": {
          "id": "FNq1tabrcjylXbSd",
          "name": "Plans-Acornhealthandsafety"
        }
      },
      "onError": "continueRegularOutput"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": false,
            "version": 2
          },
          "combinator": "and",
          "conditions": [
            {
              "id": "cond_img",
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.name }}",
              "rightValue": "\\.(jpe?g|png)$",
              "operator": {
                "type": "string",
                "operation": "regex"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "filter_image",
      "name": "Keep image attachments",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.filter",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [720, 340]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Keep only the FIRST image per project (multi-image emails).\nconst out = [];\nconst seen = new Set();\nconst items = $input.all();\nfor (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {\n  let key;\n  try { key = $('Extract N-number').itemMatching(i).json.projectNumber; }\n  catch (e) { key = items[i].json.id; }\n  if (seen.has(key)) continue;\n  seen.add(key);\n  out.push(items[i]);\n}\nreturn out;"
      },
      "id": "first_image",
      "name": "First image per project",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [940, 340]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "messageAttachment",
        "operation": "download",
        "messageId": {
          "__rl": true,
          "value": "={{ $('Extract N-number').item.json.messageId }}",
          "mode": "id"
        },
        "attachmentId": "={{ $json.id }}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.microsoftOutlook",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [1160, 340],
      "id": "download_attachment",
      "name": "Download sketch",
      "credentials": {
        "microsoftOutlookOAuth2Api": {
          "id": "FNq1tabrcjylXbSd",
          "name": "Plans-Acornhealthandsafety"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Compute ONE per-project filename and carry it in json so every downstream\n// node (SSH upload + SSH command) references the same value. Generic\n// 'Image.jpeg' attachments would otherwise collide across projects.\nconst items = $input.all();\nfor (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {\n  const pn = $('Extract N-number').itemMatching(i).json.projectNumber;\n  const b = items[i].binary && items[i].binary.data;\n  const ext = ((b && b.fileName ? b.fileName : 'x.jpg').split('.').pop() || 'jpg').toLowerCase();\n  const sketchFile = `${pn}_sketch.${ext}`;\n  if (b) b.fileName = sketchFile;\n  items[i].json = { ...items[i].json, projectNumber: pn, sketchFile };\n}\nreturn items;"
      },
      "id": "name_sketch",
      "name": "Name sketch",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [1380, 340]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "file",
        "operation": "upload",
        "path": "/tmp",
        "binaryPropertyName": "data",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "ssh_upload",
      "name": "Upload sketch (SSH)",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.ssh",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [1600, 340],
      "credentials": {
        "sshPassword": {
          "id": "ijqPYjkPkcQNqduL",
          "name": "Acorn n8n Server SSH"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "command": "=docker cp \"/tmp/{{ $('Name sketch').item.json.sketchFile }}\" plangenration:/tmp/ && docker exec plangenration python src/process_plan.py \"{{ $('Name sketch').item.json.projectNumber }}\" --image \"/tmp/{{ $('Name sketch').item.json.sketchFile }}\""
      },
      "id": "ssh_run",
      "name": "Draw plan in container (SSH)",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.ssh",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [1820, 340],
      "credentials": {
        "sshPassword": {
          "id": "ijqPYjkPkcQNqduL",
          "name": "Acorn n8n Server SSH"
        }
      },
      "continueOnFail": true
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": false,
            "version": 2
          },
          "combinator": "and",
          "conditions": [
            {
              "id": "cond_ok",
              "leftValue": "={{ /\"(ok|skipped)\":\\s*true/.test($json.stdout || '') }}",
              "rightValue": true,
              "operator": {
                "type": "boolean",
                "operation": "true",
                "singleValue": true
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "if_handled",
      "name": "Queued for review / handled?",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [2040, 340]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "message",
        "operation": "update",
        "messageId": {
          "__rl": true,
          "value": "={{ $('Extract N-number').item.json.messageId }}",
          "mode": "id"
        },
        "updateFields": {
          "isRead": true
        }
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.microsoftOutlook",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [2260, 260],
      "id": "mark_read",
      "name": "Mark email as read",
      "credentials": {
        "microsoftOutlookOAuth2Api": {
          "id": "FNq1tabrcjylXbSd",
          "name": "Plans-Acornhealthandsafety"
        }
      },
      "onError": "continueRegularOutput"
    },
    {
